  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cocoa Study Center in Ebolowa, Cameroon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of this project is to build and use a Center for Cocoa Study in Ebolowa, Cameroon, where international and African university students will work with cocoa-farming villagers to enhance economic and environmental sustainability.  Research will include these academic areas:  appropriate technology (solar-powered cocoa dryers), nutrition (status of cocoa farmers&apos; children), food technology (chocolate manufacture),  and value chain (local distribution issues around cocoa and chocolate).</narrative>
  </description>
